summary_text: 1. I grew up in a neighborhood with Mrs. Baker. 2. Mrs. Baker was known as the resident cat lady. 3. She had adopted at least twenty cats. 4. Mrs. Baker had a young grandson. 5. I was quite the tomboy back then. 6. The grandson was trying to befriend me. 7. I didn't take to him much. 8. He seemed charming until you saw his manners. 9. He had poor manners, which was off-putting. 10. He left a note saying he was going to run away. 11. Mrs. Baker came to my treehouse looking for help. 12. I talked her down from panicking. 13. I suggested we look for him before involving police. 14. We searched where his baseball cap was found. 15. We trailed more but found no trace of him. 16. We returned to the treehouse club. 17. He was sitting on a branch with a comic book. 18. Officer Dawson advised me to lay low. 19. I laid low and stayed out of sight after that incident.
